result.execSummary:
The defendant Neal R Moss was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Child Pornography, a class D felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.12(1m).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

2:42 pm  Back on the record.
2:42 pm  Court having heard the arguments and recommendations of both sides and considered SM-34 factors and Gallion which are placed on the record pronounces sentence as follows:

Eight (8) years in Wisconsin Prison System bifurcated as four (4) years Initial Confinement followed by four (4) years Extended Supervision, consecutive to 16CF205 and any other sentence.
Defendant is NOTeligible for CIP or SAP.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:

Costs including supervision fees and pornography image surcharge(s).
Must register as a sex offender for life and remain compliant.
DNA sample previously provided.  Pay DNA surcharge.

No contact with any minors including any family members without Agent permission.
Comply with any counseling as recommended by Agent including any assessments or treatment and specifically any Sex Offender Treatment programming.
Not to possess any firearms or other weapons.
